  "text": "The gRPC Health Check Protocol compliance in Envoy v1.31.2 is implemented through the following architecture:\n\n**Primary Implementation Files:**\n\n1. **GrpcHealthCheckerImpl** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h/cc) - The main gRPC health checker implementation that implements the grpc.health.v1.Health service Check RPC method. This class:\n   - Creates and manages GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession instances for each host\n   - Handles the factory pattern through GrpcHealthCheckerFactory\n   - Parses configuration including service_name and authority settings\n   - Includes the grpc::health::v1 protobuf header for HealthCheckRequest and HealthCheckResponse types\n\n2. **GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession** - The active health check session that:\n   - Implements the grpc.health.v1.Health.Check unary RPC call (path: /grpc.health.v1.Health/Check)\n   - Sends HealthCheckRequest messages with optional service name\n   - Decodes HealthCheckResponse messages and maps response status to health states\n   - Implements HTTP/2 response decoding (decodeHeaders, decodeData, decodeTrailers)\n   - Maps gRPC status codes to health check success/failure outcomes\n\n**Key Protocol Compliance Elements:**\n\n1. **HealthCheckRequest Handling** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.cc:233-238):\n   - Creates HealthCheckRequest with optional service name from configuration\n   - Serializes request using Grpc::Common::serializeToGrpcFrame()\n   - Sends as unary RPC with single message frame\n\n2. **HealthCheckResponse Status Mapping** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.cc:300-312, 365-398):\n   - isHealthCheckSucceeded(): Checks for gRPC OK status AND HealthCheckResponse.status == SERVING\n   - Handles all four response statuses: SERVING (healthy), NOT_SERVING (failure), UNKNOWN (failure), SERVICE_UNKNOWN (failure for Check method)\n   - logHealthCheckStatus(): Maps response statuses to debug strings for logging\n\n3. **HTTP-to-gRPC Status Mapping** (source/common/grpc/status.cc:6-26):\n   - Utility::httpToGrpcStatus() implements RFC mapping from HTTP response codes to gRPC status codes\n   - Handles cases where HTTP intermediaries don't understand gRPC (see https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/doc/http-grpc-status-mapping.md)\n   - Maps: 400→Internal, 401→Unauthenticated, 403→PermissionDenied, 404→Unimplemented, 429/502/503/504→Unavailable\n\n4. **gRPC Response Parsing** (source/common/grpc/common.cc):\n   - isGrpcResponseHeaders(): Validates HTTP/2 200 OK with gRPC content-type\n   - getGrpcStatus(): Extracts grpc-status header from response headers or trailers\n   - getGrpcMessage(): Extracts grpc-message header for error details\n   - Handles trailers-only gRPC responses (no data frames)\n\n5. **Protocol Frame Handling** (source/common/grpc/codec.h/cc):\n   - Decoder: Decodes gRPC frames (5-byte header + protobuf message)\n   - Frame format: 1 byte flags + 4 bytes length (big-endian) + message data\n   - Validates single frame constraint for unary RPC (error on streaming)\n   - Validates GRPC_FH_DEFAULT flag (uncompressed) for health check responses\n\n6. **Request Construction** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.cc:203-238):\n   - Uses Grpc::Common::prepareHeaders() to create proper gRPC request headers\n   - Sets path to /grpc.health.v1.Health/Check\n   - Includes service method descriptor from protobuf descriptor pool\n   - Handles optional request headers from configuration (initial_metadata)\n   - Sets grpc-timeout header using Grpc::Common::toGrpcTimeout()\n\n**Proto Integration:**\nThe implementation includes `src/proto/grpc/health/v1/health.pb.h` which provides:\n- HealthCheckRequest message type (contains service field)\n- HealthCheckResponse message type with ServingStatus enum (UNKNOWN=0, SERVING=1, NOT_SERVING=2, SERVICE_UNKNOWN=3)\n- Health service descriptor used to obtain the Check method descriptor\n\n**Base Classes:**\n- HealthCheckerImplBase (source/extensions/health_checkers/common/health_checker_base_impl.h) - Provides timing, callbacks, and host lifecycle management\n- ActiveHealthCheckSession - Base for session state management and health transition reporting\n\nThe implementation fully complies with the gRPC Health Checking Protocol (https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/doc/health-checking.md) by correctly handling the unary Check RPC, parsing response status codes, and mapping them to host health states."
